      "title": "Group Discounts: Conditions and Limits",
      "content": "Group discounts reward customers who purchase multiple tickets at once and they work best when the rules are simple and the savings are visible. A common structure is a tiered discount where buying 5 to 9 tickets gives a 10 percent reduction and 10 or more tickets unlocks a 15 percent reduction. Clearly communicate the minimum quantity required and the exact percentage saved so the buyer can calculate the benefit instantly. Set a maximum group size to protect inventory and to keep the discount from eroding profit margins; for instance you might cap the discount at 20 tickets per transaction. Define eligibility criteria such as all tickets must be for the same performance and must be purchased in a single order. If the group qualifies for a discount but the inventory is low you can offer a substitute date or a different seating zone while still honoring the discount percentage. Promote group discounts through targeted email campaigns that highlight the savings per person and include a special code that applies automatically at checkout. By framing the discount as a way to save together you encourage larger orders and foster repeat business."
